 Parse Registry Hives Using RegRipper & Registry Explorer
Learning Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Install and configure RegRipper and Registry Explorer on Linux
Extract registry hives from Windows disk images
Parse registry data to identify system artifacts
Analyze user activity and system configuration through registry analysis
Generate comprehensive reports from registry data
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command-line knowledge
Understanding of Windows registry structure
Familiarity with digital forensics concepts
Knowledge of file system navigation
Lab Environment
Al Nafi provides Linux-based cloud machines for this lab. Simply click Start Lab to access your dedicated environment. The provided Linux machine is bare metal with no pre-installed tools, so you will install all required software during the lab exercises.

Task 1: Install RegRipper and Registry Explorer
Subtask 1.1: Update System and Install Dependencies
# Update package repository
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install required dependencies
sudo apt install -y perl git python3 python3-pip wget curl unzip build-essential
Subtask 1.2: Install RegRipper
# Clone RegRipper repository
cd /opt
sudo git clone https://github.com/keydet89/RegRipper3.0.git
sudo mv RegRipper3.0 regripper
sudo chmod +x /opt/regripper/rip.pl

# Create symbolic link for easy access
sudo ln -s /opt/regripper/rip.pl /usr/local/bin/rip
Subtask 1.3: Install Registry Explorer Dependencies
# Install Wine for running Windows applications on Linux
sudo dpkg --add-architecture i386
sudo mkdir -pm755 /etc/apt/keyrings
sudo wget -O /etc/apt/keyrings/winehq-archive.key https://dl.winehq.org/wine-builds/winehq.key
sudo wget -NP /etc/apt/sources.list.d/ https://dl.winehq.org/wine-builds/ubuntu/dists/jammy/winehq-jammy.sources
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y winehq-stable

# Download Registry Explorer
cd /opt
sudo wget https://f001.backblazeb2.com/file/EricZimmermanTools/RegistryExplorer.zip
sudo unzip RegistryExplorer.zip -d registry-explorer
sudo chmod +x /opt/registry-explorer/RegistryExplorer.exe
Subtask 1.4: Create Sample Registry Hives
# Create working directory
mkdir -p ~/forensics/registry-lab
cd ~/forensics/registry-lab

# Download sample registry hives (simulated Windows registry files)
wget -O SYSTEM.hiv https://github.com/EricZimmerman/RegistryExplorer/raw/master/RegistryExplorer.Test/TestFiles/SYSTEM
wget -O SOFTWARE.hiv https://github.com/EricZimmerman/RegistryExplorer/raw/master/RegistryExplorer.Test/TestFiles/SOFTWARE
wget -O NTUSER.DAT https://github.com/EricZimmerman/RegistryExplorer/raw/master/RegistryExplorer.Test/TestFiles/NTUSER.DAT
Task 2: Parse Registry Hives with RegRipper
Subtask 2.1: Analyze SYSTEM Hive
# Parse SYSTEM hive for computer information
rip -r SYSTEM.hiv -p compname > system_analysis.txt
rip -r SYSTEM.hiv -p timezone >> system_analysis.txt
rip -r SYSTEM.hiv -p shutdown >> system_analysis.txt

# View results
cat system_analysis.txt
Subtask 2.2: Analyze SOFTWARE Hive
# Extract installed programs and version information
rip -r SOFTWARE.hiv -p uninstall > software_analysis.txt
rip -r SOFTWARE.hiv -p version >> software_analysis.txt
rip -r SOFTWARE.hiv -p winver >> software_analysis.txt

# View results
head -20 software_analysis.txt
Subtask 2.3: Analyze User Registry (NTUSER.DAT)
# Extract user activity artifacts
rip -r NTUSER.DAT -p userassist > user_analysis.txt
rip -r NTUSER.DAT -p recentdocs >> user_analysis.txt
rip -r NTUSER.DAT -p runmru >> user_analysis.txt

# View user activity
cat user_analysis.txt
Subtask 2.4: Generate Comprehensive Report
# Create comprehensive analysis script
cat > analyze_all.sh << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash
echo "=== SYSTEM ANALYSIS ===" > full_report.txt
rip -r SYSTEM.hiv -p compname >> full_report.txt
rip -r SYSTEM.hiv -p services >> full_report.txt
echo -e "\n=== SOFTWARE ANALYSIS ===" >> full_report.txt
rip -r SOFTWARE.hiv -p uninstall >> full_report.txt
echo -e "\n=== USER ANALYSIS ===" >> full_report.txt
rip -r NTUSER.DAT -p userassist >> full_report.txt
rip -r NTUSER.DAT -p recentdocs >> full_report.txt
echo "Analysis complete. Report saved to full_report.txt"
EOF

chmod +x analyze_all.sh
./analyze_all.sh
Task 3: Extract and Analyze Registry Artifacts
Subtask 3.1: Extract Network Configuration
# Analyze network settings from SYSTEM hive
rip -r SYSTEM.hiv -p nic > network_config.txt
rip -r SYSTEM.hiv -p tcpip >> network_config.txt

echo "Network Configuration Analysis:"
cat network_config.txt
Subtask 3.2: Extract USB Device History
# Extract USB device connection history
rip -r SYSTEM.hiv -p usbstor > usb_devices.txt
rip -r SYSTEM.hiv -p mountdev >> usb_devices.txt

echo "USB Device History:"
cat usb_devices.txt
Subtask 3.3: Extract Browser Artifacts
# Extract browser-related registry entries
rip -r NTUSER.DAT -p ie_main > browser_artifacts.txt
rip -r NTUSER.DAT -p typedurls >> browser_artifacts.txt

echo "Browser Artifacts:"
cat browser_artifacts.txt
Subtask 3.4: Extract Startup Programs
# Identify programs that run at startup
rip -r SOFTWARE.hiv -p run > startup_programs.txt
rip -r NTUSER.DAT -p run >> startup_programs.txt

echo "Startup Programs:"
cat startup_programs.txt
Task 4: Advanced Registry Analysis
Subtask 4.1: Timeline Analysis
# Create timeline of registry modifications
rip -r SYSTEM.hiv -f ntuser | head -20 > timeline.txt
rip -r SOFTWARE.hiv -f ntuser | head -20 >> timeline.txt

echo "Registry Timeline (First 40 entries):"
cat timeline.txt
Subtask 4.2: Search for Specific Artifacts
# Search for specific keywords in registry
grep -i "malware\|virus\|trojan" full_report.txt > security_findings.txt
grep -i "password\|credential" full_report.txt >> security_findings.txt

echo "Security-Related Findings:"
cat security_findings.txt
Subtask 4.3: Export Registry Keys
# Create script to export specific registry paths
cat > export_keys.sh << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash
echo "Exporting critical registry keys..."
rip -r SYSTEM.hiv -p services | grep -A5 -B5 "svchost" > critical_services.txt
rip -r SOFTWARE.hiv -p uninstall | grep -i "microsoft" > microsoft_software.txt
echo "Export complete."
EOF

chmod +x export_keys.sh
./export_keys.sh
Task 5: Registry Explorer Analysis (Alternative Method)
Subtask 5.1: Launch Registry Explorer
# Initialize Wine environment
winecfg

# Launch Registry Explorer (in background)
cd /opt/registry-explorer
wine RegistryExplorer.exe &
Subtask 5.2: Manual Registry Exploration
# Create analysis notes file
cat > registry_explorer_notes.txt << 'EOF'
Registry Explorer Analysis Notes:
================================

1. Load SYSTEM.hiv:
   - Navigate to ControlSet001\Services
   - Document running services
   
2. Load SOFTWARE.hiv:
