Verification and Testing
Verify RegRipper Installation
# Test RegRipper functionality
rip -l | head -10
echo "RegRipper plugins available: $(rip -l | wc -l)"
Verify Analysis Completeness
# Check if all analysis files were created
required_files=("system_analysis.txt" "software_analysis.txt" "user_analysis.txt" "network_config.txt" "usb_devices.txt" "final_report.txt")

echo "Checking analysis completeness:"
for file in "${required_files[@]}"; do
    if [ -f "$file" ]; then
        echo "✓ $file exists ($(wc -l < "$file") lines)"
    else
        echo "✗ $file missing"
    fi
done
Troubleshooting
Common Issues and Solutions
RegRipper not found:

# Verify installation path
ls -la /opt/regripper/
# Recreate symbolic link if needed
sudo ln -sf /opt/regripper/rip.pl /usr/local/bin/rip
Wine configuration issues:

# Reconfigure Wine
winecfg
# Set Windows version to Windows 10
Permission errors:

# Fix permissions
sudo chown -R $USER:$USER ~/forensics/
chmod +x *.sh
